records.nl_statement: Suppose that $f(x)=\sum_{i=0}^{\infty} c_{i} x^{i}$ is a power series for which each coefficient $c_{i}$ is 0 or 1 . Show that if $f(2 / 3)=3 / 2$, then $f(1 / 2)$ must be irrational.

  (hc : ∀ n, c n = 0 ∨ c n = 1)

  Irrational (f (1/2)) :=
